          <h2>Why carbon footprint matters</h2>
          <p>When we talk about a <strong>carbon footprint</strong>, we mean the total greenhouse gases (GHGs) ‚Äî especially carbon dioxide (CO‚ÇÇ) ‚Äî released directly or indirectly by our activities. These emissions accumulate in the atmosphere, trapping heat and driving changes in global climate systems.</p>

          <div class="blockquote">
            <strong>Quick takeaway:</strong> Small personal and collective changes add up. Reducing energy waste, choosing lower-carbon transport, and shifting diets all lower the total emissions released into the atmosphere.
